abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Papers of Nicholas Wahl document Wahl's contributions as a student, professor and academic administrator from 1949 to 1995. The majority of materials document his career as professor and director at New York University's Institute of French Studies from 1978 to 1996. Wahl's publications, speeches, research, course material, and correspondence reflect his lifetime study of French politics and society, in particular his expertise on former French President Charles De Gaulle.

p.value: Please contact the University Archivists with specific questions regarding restrictions.

Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); Nicholas Wahl Papers; MC 146; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.

<list>
                    <item>Nicholas Wahl, Biographical File, New York University Archives, Archives H.</item>
                    <item> "In Memoriam Nicholas Wahl," 
                        <title render="italic">French Politics and Society</title>, Vol. 14, No. 4, Autumn 1996.</item>
                </list>

Contains administrative correspondence, syllabi, and other materials related to both courses Wahl took as a graduate student at Harvard and those he taught at Harvard, Princeton, and NYU, as well as other institutions at which he served as a visiting professor.
